The All Progressives Congress in Rivers State has continued to lose key members a few months to the 2023 general elections. The latest member of the party to resign is the former Commissioner for Information, Ibim Seminitari. Seminitari was a commissioner under the former Governor, Rotimi Amaechi and also served as the sole administrator of the Niger Delta Development Commission, NDDC. In a letter personally signed by her, the former commissioner thanked her former party for the opportunities it presented for her to serve in different capacities Seminitariâ€™s announcement comes a few days after former Commissioner for Youths in the state, Dawari George, left the party.